# .vldf

<file>.<format>.<vldf>

A new compression scheme
(format dependant, so there is no standalone vldf parser)

Instead of storing the data itself, store the index into a table of all valid data.
(Big-Endian) (Add the max for the n-1 digits for any n-digit number)

example.utf8.vldf	example.utf8
EOF			EOF
00 EOF			00 EOF
01 EOF			01 EOF
...			...
80 EOF			C2 80 EOF (first valid 2-byte)
81 EOF			C2 81 EOF
...
9E EOF			E0 80 80 EOF (first valid 3-byte)

<Title Text>:
For formats that don't have an easy way to determine Nth valid, just iterate through all possible. you sacrificed speed
for compression long, long ago.

